WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:02.636
Previously on
"The Good Doctor"...

00:02.670 --> 00:05.473
Dr. Coyle --
He's a little too friendly.

00:05.506 --> 00:06.540
I'm sure he's just trying
to establish a rapport.

00:06.574 --> 00:08.176
Coyle:
I give great massages.

00:08.209 --> 00:09.510
And I'll make a killer omelet
in the morning.

00:09.543 --> 00:10.778
That's really
inappropriate.

00:10.811 --> 00:12.446
I said no.

00:12.480 --> 00:13.381
You're approaching
insubordination.

00:13.414 --> 00:15.483
Jared: You have to file
a complaint with HR.

00:15.516 --> 00:18.519
They will shift the blame
onto me. Like you did.

00:19.720 --> 00:20.521
I've just been fired

00:20.554 --> 00:21.555
for physically assaulting
an employee.

00:21.589 --> 00:23.624
So, why do I need to quit my job
to have a family?

00:23.657 --> 00:26.060
Agreed. She can be
a great lawyer and a great mom.

00:26.094 --> 00:27.295
I don't want to have kids.

00:27.328 --> 00:29.297
Shaun:
I don't need a therapist.

00:29.330 --> 00:31.232
I want to make
my own decisions.

00:31.265 --> 00:32.233
I am done talking.

00:32.266 --> 00:33.367
Now let's go.
No. N-No.

00:33.401 --> 00:34.402
I don't want help!

00:34.435 --> 00:35.303
Melissa:
Where would he go?

00:35.336 --> 00:36.737
Is there a place
he likes to hang out?

00:36.770 --> 00:38.139
I mean, he's not
at the hospital.

00:38.172 --> 00:39.473
And there used to be
a picture here.

00:39.507 --> 00:41.542
It means
he's not coming back.

00:42.276 --> 00:44.712
[ Knock on door ]

00:44.745 --> 00:46.347
Hi. Good morning.

00:46.380 --> 00:48.116
I'm Aaron Glassman.
Dr. Glassman.

00:48.149 --> 00:49.450
I work with Shaun.

00:49.483 --> 00:51.319
Hi. Nice to meet you.

00:51.352 --> 00:53.554
It's nice to meet you, too.
May I speak with him, please?

00:53.587 --> 00:56.357
Uh, Shaun isn't here.

00:56.390 --> 01:01.529
I know you've been helping
Shaun, and I appreciate that,

01:01.562 --> 01:03.697
but I really need
to speak with him immediately.

01:03.731 --> 01:07.135
I'll definitely let him know
when I see him next.

01:07.835 --> 01:09.237
I'm -- I'm sorry.

01:09.270 --> 01:10.304
What the hell
are you doing?

01:10.338 --> 01:11.572
Shaun,
I know you're in here.

01:11.605 --> 01:14.208
I just --
I just want to talk, please.

01:14.242 --> 01:15.476
You are way out of line.

01:15.509 --> 01:17.811
Shaun, you have
responsibilities.

01:17.845 --> 01:18.946
We've got to
sort this out.

01:18.979 --> 01:21.149
You have five seconds
to get the hell out of here...

01:21.182 --> 01:22.383
-Shaun.
-...or I'm calling the police.

01:22.416 --> 01:23.784
-Shaun, I just --
-What are --

01:23.817 --> 01:26.354
I just want to...

01:26.387 --> 01:29.223
-Five...
-Shaun.

01:29.257 --> 01:30.724
Shaun,
she's calling the police.

01:30.758 --> 01:32.293
-...four...
-Is that what you want?

01:32.326 --> 01:33.894
Lea: ...three...

01:33.927 --> 01:35.296
...two...
-Okay, okay.

01:35.329 --> 01:36.764
-...one.
-Okay, okay, I'm leaving.

01:36.797 --> 01:40.134
It's just that
Shaun has a-a tendency

01:40.168 --> 01:41.302
to run away
from conflict.

01:41.335 --> 01:43.504
And in Casper
and medical school,

01:43.537 --> 01:45.906
people will give you
a little bit of slack, but it --

01:45.939 --> 01:47.708
now he's in a very
hard-to-get job

01:47.741 --> 01:49.577
in a very competitive
environment

01:49.610 --> 01:51.879
where people do not give you
a second chance.

01:51.912 --> 01:56.550
Still, not cool.

02:00.254 --> 02:02.856
If you speak with him
[clears throat]

02:02.890 --> 02:04.358
will you call me,
please?

02:04.392 --> 02:06.494
Out.

02:08.496 --> 02:10.398
Yeah.

02:10.431 --> 02:13.434
[ Door opens, closes ]

02:13.467 --> 02:15.169
[ Sighs ]

02:19.307 --> 02:21.275
[ Lea sighs ]

02:21.309 --> 02:23.911
So, what's your plan now?

02:26.414 --> 02:29.250
I don't know.

02:29.283 --> 02:32.220
-- Captions by VITAC --

02:32.253 --> 02:39.227
**

02:39.260 --> 02:42.196
I gotta say, he seems like
a nebby, old jerk.

02:42.230 --> 02:43.197
And a bully.

02:43.231 --> 02:44.632
What's "nebby"?

02:44.665 --> 02:46.967
Nosey.
It's a Pittsburgh thing.

02:47.000 --> 02:48.636
I mean,
you're a grown man.

02:48.669 --> 02:50.904
If you don't want to talk to
him, it's none of his business.

02:50.938 --> 02:54.975
San Jose is too big.

02:55.008 --> 02:57.578
I get not liking San Jose.

02:57.611 --> 02:59.313
I'm not the biggest fan myself,
but --

02:59.347 --> 03:01.682
I don't want to see
a therapist.

03:01.715 --> 03:03.484
So don't.

03:05.719 --> 03:08.456
I should go back to Casper.

03:08.489 --> 03:09.790
I have a rule.

03:09.823 --> 03:13.294
Never make an important
decision while you are angry,

03:13.327 --> 03:17.265
upset, high, or right before
or after having sex.

03:17.298 --> 03:19.800
Okay, you are overworked,
stressed out,

03:19.833 --> 03:20.834
and pissed off
at your boss.

03:20.868 --> 03:23.904
Now is not the time
to be making a big decision.

03:23.937 --> 03:27.441
You need to take a break,
clear your head.

03:27.475 --> 03:28.876
You need a vacation.

03:28.909 --> 03:32.680
I have to work five more months
before I earn a vacation.

03:32.713 --> 03:34.782
So call in sick.

03:34.815 --> 03:36.617
I'm not sick.

03:36.650 --> 03:38.786
[ Sighs ]
You're so adorable.

03:38.819 --> 03:41.622
You don't have to be sick
to call in sick.

03:41.655 --> 03:44.292
Ah, I have so much
to teach you, Grasshopper.

03:44.325 --> 03:47.428
And I'm gonna start with
a good, old-fashioned road trip.

03:47.461 --> 03:49.029
It's the perfect way
to get your mojo back.

03:49.062 --> 03:51.465
And when we return, you're
gonna know exactly what to do

03:51.499 --> 03:55.336
about San Jose, therapy,
and Glassy the Grouch.

03:55.369 --> 03:56.304
And all you have to do

03:56.337 --> 03:58.839
to attain this superior wisdom
and knowledge

03:58.872 --> 04:05.946
is to call...in...sick.

04:09.950 --> 04:12.553
Okay. Okay. I will.

04:12.586 --> 04:15.656
**

04:15.689 --> 04:18.058
Dr. Melendez.
Got a case for you.

04:18.091 --> 04:19.159
My schedule's
pretty packed today.

04:19.192 --> 04:22.496
It's a patient of mine.
She needs a kidney transplant.

04:22.530 --> 04:24.465
You have a donor?

04:24.498 --> 04:26.800
Her identical twin --
a perfect DNA match.

04:26.834 --> 04:27.901
Why is she
a patient of yours?

04:27.935 --> 04:30.738
I put balloon tissue expanders
under both girls' scalps

04:30.771 --> 04:32.873
to prepare them
for the separation surgery.

04:32.906 --> 04:34.408
Separation surgery?

04:34.442 --> 04:39.380
**

04:39.413 --> 04:42.750
It's in six months, after they
recover from the transplant.

04:42.783 --> 04:44.051
Of course,
if you're too busy...

04:44.084 --> 04:46.554
No. I'm in.

04:48.956 --> 04:51.659
Where's Murphy?
-He's not here yet.

04:51.692 --> 04:54.428
Wrong day to be late.
We're already shorthanded.

04:55.128 --> 04:57.798
Actually, I wanted
to talk to you about that.
I did not fire Kalu.

04:57.831 --> 05:00.401
And if you have a problem
with it, talk to Andrews.

05:00.434 --> 05:03.804
Although, if you want my advice,
don't have a problem with it.

05:04.738 --> 05:06.907
Andrews is waiting
to brief us on a new case.

05:06.940 --> 05:10.110
It's a kidney transplant
on craniopagus twins.

05:10.143 --> 05:11.879
Conjoined?

05:11.912 --> 05:13.013
They're connected
at the skull.

05:13.046 --> 05:16.450
Their entire renal-vascular
systems are interdependent.

05:16.750 --> 05:17.918
Cool.

05:17.951 --> 05:20.421
Hey. Have either of you
talked to Shaun?

05:20.454 --> 05:23.557
-No.
-No, which isn't unusual.

05:23.591 --> 05:24.558
Is anything wrong?

05:24.592 --> 05:27.995
No, no, not with Shaun.
It's a family emergency.

05:28.028 --> 05:30.531
He's gonna be out
for a few days.
He's supposed to
get approval

05:30.564 --> 05:32.700
for any personal days
from his attending.

05:32.733 --> 05:34.101
Right, which is why
I'm checking in.

05:34.134 --> 05:37.671
I think he thought it was enough
just to notify me.

05:38.572 --> 05:44.044
**

05:44.077 --> 05:49.717
**

05:49.750 --> 05:50.818
You call in sick?

05:53.454 --> 05:55.489
I'm ready to go.

05:55.523 --> 05:57.391
[ Zipper zips ]

05:57.425 --> 05:59.126
No, you're not.

06:03.964 --> 06:06.734
You're gonna need more than
a family photo and a toothbrush.

06:06.767 --> 06:07.768
Go pack.

06:07.801 --> 06:08.936
Uh, where are we going?

06:08.969 --> 06:10.504
Wherever the car takes us.

06:10.538 --> 06:11.572
I don't like the beach.

06:11.605 --> 06:13.941
Okay,
I will let the car know.

06:15.175 --> 06:17.044
Even with
your cardiovascular issues,

06:17.077 --> 06:19.813
a kidney transplant
is a relatively safe procedure,

06:19.847 --> 06:21.715
especially since,
with identical twins,

06:21.749 --> 06:23.751
there's no chance
for organ rejection.

06:23.784 --> 06:25.786
Just make sure you keep straight
which one's which.

06:25.819 --> 06:29.523
The charming, pretty one
has the good kidneys.

06:29.557 --> 06:32.125
Don't worry.
We always triple confirm.

06:32.159 --> 06:34.628
And we put everything
in writing.

06:34.662 --> 06:36.464
And you're both charming
and pretty.

06:36.497 --> 06:38.131
-Mm-hmm.
-It was a joke, Mom.

06:38.165 --> 06:39.933
Glenda: And smart.

06:39.967 --> 06:41.502
They're gonna be Ivy Leaguers
in the fall.

06:41.535 --> 06:43.737
Yale and Harvard.
-Wow.

06:43.771 --> 06:45.706
Mom, you don't have to tell
everyone you meet

06:45.739 --> 06:48.008
where we're going to college.
-Yes, I do.

06:48.041 --> 06:50.544
That's awesome.
Congratulations.

06:50.578 --> 06:53.447
So, who's going where?

06:53.481 --> 06:55.549
What do you think?
She's totally obnoxious

06:55.583 --> 06:57.050
and thinks she's way funnier
than she is.

06:57.084 --> 07:00.053
-Definitely Harvard.
-Mm-hmm.

07:00.087 --> 07:02.456
Hey, don't make me start
mocking your tattoo.

07:02.490 --> 07:05.058
[ Both laugh ]

07:07.528 --> 07:09.229
I thought you would have
your entire apartment

07:09.262 --> 07:10.263
strapped to your back.

07:10.297 --> 07:13.567
It takes me a long time
to pack.
That's good.

07:13.601 --> 07:16.036
An anal-retentive packer
is the exact type of person

07:16.069 --> 07:17.538
I'd want operating
on me.

07:17.571 --> 07:19.840
Lea, this --
this is your car.

07:19.873 --> 07:21.942
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
We're gonna take my other one.

07:21.975 --> 07:25.813
Okay.
What do you do at work?

07:25.846 --> 07:28.582
Do you really care what I do,
or do you just want to know

07:28.616 --> 07:31.485
how someone with such a crappy
apartment can afford two cars?

07:31.519 --> 07:35.589
I just want to know
how you can afford two cars.

07:35.623 --> 07:37.658
Hmm.

07:37.691 --> 07:38.926
Yeah, I can't.

07:38.959 --> 07:41.161
Uh, my Grandpa Rod died
last year,

07:41.194 --> 07:44.865
and he left me
his most prized possession.

07:44.898 --> 07:46.900
[ Chuckles ]

07:46.934 --> 07:50.804
It's
the S-Striped Tomato.

07:50.838 --> 07:52.172
Oh, my God.
You like "Starsky & Hutch"?

07:52.205 --> 07:53.907
It's okay.

07:53.941 --> 07:57.077
A meticulous packer
and a "Starsky & Hutch" fan.

07:57.110 --> 07:58.646
Grandpa Rod
would have loved you.

07:58.679 --> 08:05.986
**

08:06.019 --> 08:09.857
Okay. This is it.
The road.

08:09.890 --> 08:11.592
You sure
you want to do this?

08:11.625 --> 08:15.095
Speak now
or forever hold your peace.

08:15.763 --> 08:17.698
I'm sure.

08:18.832 --> 08:20.634
Let's go, Lea.

08:20.668 --> 08:21.669
[ Tires squeal ]

08:21.702 --> 08:22.870
Here we go!
[ Laughs ]

08:22.903 --> 08:28.642
**

08:33.113 --> 08:38.118
[ Knock on door ]
I hear Murphy's AWOL.

08:38.151 --> 08:40.554
He's taking
a few personal days.

08:40.588 --> 08:41.822
Unapproved personal days.

08:41.855 --> 08:42.956
I approved them.

08:42.990 --> 08:44.157
It's not your job
to approve them.

08:44.191 --> 08:47.294
Or to say you approved them
to cover up the fact

08:47.327 --> 08:50.330
that Murphy's frequent tardiness
has escalated to absences.

08:50.363 --> 08:53.967
What do you want me to do,
take a polygraph?

08:54.001 --> 08:56.069
How about we jump into
enhanced interrogation?

08:56.103 --> 08:59.640
Here, how about this?
Do you want me to turn this on?

08:59.673 --> 09:02.175
When the board was reconsidering
your hiring of Murphy,

09:02.209 --> 09:06.747
you assured us that if he was
anything less than excellent,

09:06.780 --> 09:08.649
he'd be dismissed
and you would resign.

09:08.682 --> 09:09.883
I trust
you remember that.

09:09.917 --> 09:13.153
I wouldn't have your movers
pack up your office just yet.

09:13.186 --> 09:15.155
You can't protect Murphy
forever.

09:15.188 --> 09:20.293
At some point, he needs
to succeed or fail on his own.

09:20.327 --> 09:24.164
**

09:24.197 --> 09:27.100
J.L.: Okay, that's three hours
on the warm ischemia clock

09:27.134 --> 09:29.202
of the transplanted kidney.

09:29.236 --> 09:32.272
Melendez: The ureter is attached
to the bladder.

09:32.305 --> 09:36.176
How's the kidney's placement
in the iliac fossa?

09:37.144 --> 09:39.246
No kinking or twisting
of the renal vessel.

09:39.279 --> 09:41.615
Good.

09:42.382 --> 09:44.718
You ready to close?

09:45.719 --> 09:47.688
Yes.

09:48.421 --> 09:52.125
Your best bet is a continuous
suture along the fascial layer.

09:52.159 --> 09:54.728
Suture.

09:56.096 --> 09:57.197
[ Alarm beeping ]

09:57.230 --> 09:59.332
Donor's pressure's
dropping.

09:59.366 --> 10:00.768
Okay, up the oxygen.

10:00.801 --> 10:02.102
Jenny must be bleeding
internally.

10:02.135 --> 10:03.270
We're gonna have to
open her back up.

10:03.303 --> 10:05.005
Staple remover.

10:05.038 --> 10:11.211
**

10:12.079 --> 10:14.748
I like trees.

10:14.782 --> 10:16.750
Yeah?
What else do you like?

10:16.784 --> 10:18.418
Besides reading
medical journals

10:18.451 --> 10:21.354
and watching reruns
of old cop shows?

10:21.388 --> 10:23.691
[ Chuckles ]
-I like you.

10:23.724 --> 10:25.993
Well, who wouldn't?
I'm very likeable.

10:26.026 --> 10:28.729
Why don't you like
San Jose?

10:28.762 --> 10:31.098
Everyone's
so competitive here.

10:31.131 --> 10:34.001
You know, if you didn't make
a million by 30,

10:34.034 --> 10:35.068
you're a total loser.

10:35.102 --> 10:37.370
I don't need $1 million.

10:37.404 --> 10:40.440
I don't even think
I need $90,000, but...

10:40.473 --> 10:42.876
You know what we both need
are some tunes.

10:42.910 --> 10:44.277
What's your preferred
driving music?

10:44.311 --> 10:47.414
M-Music -- No. N--
I don't like music. No. No.

10:47.447 --> 10:50.884
What? No, no.
Not okay.

10:50.918 --> 10:53.120
Okay, I will give you a pass
on not liking the beach

10:53.153 --> 10:54.254
because you're cute

10:54.287 --> 10:56.790
and I might need you to do
brain surgery on me someday,

10:56.824 --> 10:59.693
but not liking music --
unacceptable.

10:59.727 --> 11:00.694
I won't have it.

11:00.728 --> 11:02.429
Are you being sarcastic?

11:02.462 --> 11:05.165
No. I'm being...

11:05.198 --> 11:08.001
I actually don't know the word
for it, but my point stands.

11:08.035 --> 11:10.003
Music is amazing.

11:10.037 --> 11:12.205
You know, I remember
every important thing

11:12.239 --> 11:13.306
that has ever happened
to me

11:13.340 --> 11:17.244
based on what song
I was listening to at the time.

11:17.277 --> 11:19.880
I remember smells.

11:19.913 --> 11:23.450
Like our parking garage
smells like fabric softener,

11:23.483 --> 11:26.987
and when my brother died,
it smelled like burnt food.

11:27.487 --> 11:31.725
Oh, my God. I'm so sorry.
I had no idea.

11:31.759 --> 11:36.864
How did he, um...
if you don't mind me asking?

11:37.197 --> 11:40.100
My father was mean.

11:40.133 --> 11:44.805
He killed my pet, so my brother
and I, we ran away.

11:44.838 --> 11:46.840
Then he fell off a train
we were playing on,

11:46.874 --> 11:48.842
hit his head, and died.

11:50.477 --> 11:54.414
I never went back home.

11:54.447 --> 11:58.952
Dr. Glassman has watched out
for me ever since.

11:59.887 --> 12:05.993
Okay, so, maybe he's not
that much of a nebby jerk.

12:07.961 --> 12:11.264
What are you smelling
right now?

12:12.265 --> 12:14.935
Pine trees.

12:16.069 --> 12:18.538
Mm.
I'm never gonna forget

12:18.571 --> 12:20.473
that when you told me
about your brother and your dad,

12:20.507 --> 12:22.876
it smelled
like pine trees.

12:22.910 --> 12:25.012
But I don't want you
to ever forget

12:25.045 --> 12:27.915
that right after you told me,
we were listening to...

12:27.948 --> 12:29.182
[ Heavy metal blares ]

12:29.216 --> 12:31.418
Ouch. No.
Do not remember that.

12:31.451 --> 12:33.153
[ Singing in Spanish ]
Or that.

12:33.186 --> 12:34.487
No, thank you.

12:34.521 --> 12:37.057
* ...that again, I say it -- *
Nope. Not feeling it.

12:37.090 --> 12:40.928
* ...the satellites
in the fuse box, too *
Ooh, so good.

12:40.961 --> 12:44.564
* Our sharp teeth
are the only light *
This is the one
you will not forget.

12:44.597 --> 12:45.732
Do not forget this.

12:45.765 --> 12:47.801
* I drank the whole moon dry *
* Moon dry

12:47.835 --> 12:49.436
* 'Cause all my friends
are metalheads *

12:49.469 --> 12:51.204
* Swear they'd never
catch us dead *

12:51.238 --> 12:54.374
* Split up
when the police come *

12:54.407 --> 12:58.211
* Yeah, running
used to get me high, high *

12:58.245 --> 13:03.116
* Now I only feel tired *

13:03.150 --> 13:06.820
**

13:06.854 --> 13:08.956
Jenny had a post-op
renal-vein rupture.

13:08.989 --> 13:11.458
We were able to repair it
before she lost too much blood.

13:11.491 --> 13:12.926
Both your vitals
are stable now,

13:12.960 --> 13:14.862
and Katie's new kidney
is functioning well.

13:14.895 --> 13:16.263
Thank God.

13:16.296 --> 13:19.466
Will her ruptured vein
have any effect on our
separation surgery?

13:19.499 --> 13:20.600
It better not.

13:20.633 --> 13:22.335
Katie, I love you,
but if I have to spend

13:22.369 --> 13:23.837
one minute more
than I have to

13:23.871 --> 13:26.273
watching you practicing
some Mozart song --

13:26.306 --> 13:29.042
They're not songs.
They're concertos.
Pbht!

13:29.076 --> 13:32.145
Don't worry.
Six months is still the plan.

13:32.179 --> 13:35.015
[ Sighs ]

13:41.588 --> 13:44.191
[ Door closes ]

13:44.224 --> 13:45.225
[ Sighs ]

13:45.258 --> 13:48.395
Look, what I did
was incredibly unprofessional

13:48.428 --> 13:52.032
and just...inexcusable.

13:52.065 --> 13:55.102
But I'm guessing
you're gonna give one anyway.

13:55.135 --> 13:56.636
No.

13:56.669 --> 14:01.174
No, just an explanation
and a, uh...request.

14:02.342 --> 14:04.011
It could help me
to convince Andrews

14:04.044 --> 14:05.278
I deserve
a second chance.

14:05.312 --> 14:09.482
Okay.
Let's hear the explanation.

14:09.950 --> 14:13.153
Dr. Browne and I are...
seeing each other.

14:13.186 --> 14:15.956
Look, if you could just
put yourself in my shoes.

14:15.989 --> 14:18.992
A woman I care about tells me
a guy harassed her,

14:19.026 --> 14:20.560
and, even worse,
she tells me it's my fault

14:20.593 --> 14:23.663
because I was too --
too stupidly insensitive

14:23.696 --> 14:25.165
to understand
what she was going through.

14:25.198 --> 14:28.568
I felt like crap.

14:28.601 --> 14:34.007
And like an idiot,
I...tried to make it up to her.

14:36.944 --> 14:40.347
All I'm asking for
is just a little understanding.

14:41.114 --> 14:42.282
Wouldn't you have done
the same thing?

14:42.315 --> 14:47.955
**

14:47.988 --> 14:50.057
Not my problem.

14:53.326 --> 14:54.161
Claire: Yeah?

14:54.194 --> 14:56.329
Jenny's bradycardic
and hypotensive.

14:56.363 --> 14:58.231
-What's happening?
-She was fine a minute ago.

14:58.265 --> 15:00.367
We were talking, then
she started to have
trouble breathing.

15:00.400 --> 15:03.570
[ Monitor beeping ]

15:04.571 --> 15:06.339
Jenny's heart
is failing.

15:07.740 --> 15:08.708
No pulse.

15:08.741 --> 15:10.543
She's in V-tach.
Grab the cart, page Melendez.

15:10.577 --> 15:13.913
[ Alarm beeping rapidly ]

15:21.454 --> 15:22.455
Jenny's stable.

15:23.490 --> 15:24.724
I have her on beta blockers
and vasodilators,

15:24.757 --> 15:26.293
but it's not
gonna be enough.

15:26.326 --> 15:27.527
Renal-vein rupture
must have caused

15:27.560 --> 15:29.396
her already weak heart
to deteriorate.

15:29.429 --> 15:32.065
She's in end-stage failure.
I'll get her
on the transplant registry.

15:32.099 --> 15:34.734
What are we talking?
Months? Weeks?
Days.

15:34.767 --> 15:37.504
We're not gonna find
a donor heart in a few days.

15:40.273 --> 15:43.676
We could disconnect her
from the other body

15:43.710 --> 15:46.679
her heart is partially
oxygenating the blood for.

15:48.115 --> 15:49.349
I was already pushing
the envelope

15:49.382 --> 15:50.517
to do
the separation surgery

15:50.550 --> 15:52.485
six months
after a kidney transplant.

15:52.519 --> 15:55.155
Do you really think they could
handle it one day after?

15:56.023 --> 15:58.725
It may be our only choice.

16:01.361 --> 16:02.329
Yeah.

16:02.362 --> 16:04.998
[ Cellphone chimes ]

16:06.366 --> 16:08.601
His calls are an even bigger
buzzkill than this rain

16:08.635 --> 16:11.038
and defeating the whole purpose
of this trip.

16:11.071 --> 16:12.572
Okay.

16:12.605 --> 16:17.677
Residents are not supposed to
turn off their phones.

16:17.710 --> 16:19.279
How about we make a deal?

16:19.312 --> 16:23.216
If you turn off your phone,
I'll let you drive.

16:23.250 --> 16:26.619
I don't have
a driver's license.
I know.

16:26.653 --> 16:29.656
I've always wanted
to learn to drive.
I know.

16:29.689 --> 16:33.026
Dr. Glassman --
he never wanted me to.
I know.

16:33.060 --> 16:34.127
Actually,
I didn't know that,

16:34.161 --> 16:37.097
but that definitely sounds
like Glassy.

16:39.132 --> 16:40.067
Okay.

16:40.100 --> 16:42.035
Yeah? [ Giggles ]

16:42.069 --> 16:47.807
**

16:47.840 --> 16:49.376
You're doing awesome.

16:49.409 --> 16:52.145
You're a natural.

16:52.179 --> 16:53.480
Thank you.

16:53.513 --> 16:56.083
I think so, too.

16:56.816 --> 16:59.152
Blinker.

16:59.186 --> 17:03.256
All right,
now make this left turn.

17:03.290 --> 17:04.691
Okay,
don't circle this time.

17:04.724 --> 17:08.161
Just keep going straight.

17:10.197 --> 17:12.565
[ Brakes squeal ]
What are you stopping for?

17:12.599 --> 17:15.368
You want me
to go out on the street?

17:15.768 --> 17:19.372
It's where the car
wants to go.

17:19.406 --> 17:21.174
Come on.

17:21.208 --> 17:23.843
What's the worst thing
that could happen?

17:23.876 --> 17:28.648
I could run over someone
and kill them.

17:28.681 --> 17:31.184
You have autism.
You're not blind.

17:31.218 --> 17:32.519
And I'll be right here
with you.

17:32.552 --> 17:34.587
Mm-hmm.

17:34.621 --> 17:39.559
**

17:39.592 --> 17:42.729
Half Dome, here we come.

17:42.762 --> 17:43.863
Can I turn on the radio?

17:43.896 --> 17:46.499
-No! No, thank you.
-Okay, okay.

17:46.533 --> 17:52.272
**

17:52.305 --> 17:57.844
**

17:57.877 --> 17:59.312
Nice.

17:59.346 --> 18:04.217
**

18:04.251 --> 18:06.686
We believe moving up
the separation surgery

18:06.719 --> 18:08.655
will lighten the load
on Jenny's heart,

18:08.688 --> 18:10.257
maybe allow it
to recover a bit

18:10.290 --> 18:12.525
so a transplant won't even
be necessary in the future.

18:12.559 --> 18:14.561
It is higher risk
for Katie now,

18:14.594 --> 18:16.863
given that her new kidney
is still not fully functional.

18:16.896 --> 18:19.532
What do you think
we should do?

18:19.566 --> 18:21.868
It's your bodies.
Your decision.

18:21.901 --> 18:24.204
-Mom, stop it.
-No, I'm serious.

18:24.237 --> 18:28.241
I raised you both to be strong
and independent, and you are.

18:28.275 --> 18:32.712
So whatever you decide,
I'll support.

18:35.282 --> 18:37.417
Let's do it.

18:37.450 --> 18:39.786
Go ahead.
Chop us in half.

18:39.819 --> 18:41.788
-[ Chuckles ]
-Katie?

18:41.821 --> 18:43.456
We obviously need
both your consent.

18:43.490 --> 18:45.725
-Okay.
-You sure?

18:45.758 --> 18:47.760
You want to talk more?
Have any questions?

18:47.794 --> 18:51.364
No. I'm good.
Let's do it.

18:54.901 --> 18:56.569
Shaun: I want a car.

18:56.603 --> 18:57.804
So get one.

18:57.837 --> 18:58.971
You've been driving
a half-hour,

18:59.005 --> 19:01.574
and you're already better than
half the people in San Jose.

19:01.608 --> 19:04.511
I get distracted
when I'm alone.

19:04.544 --> 19:06.646
That's why I miss my bus
sometimes.

19:06.679 --> 19:10.283
Dr. Glassman thinks
I'd do the same thing driving.

19:10.317 --> 19:12.485
He's probably right.

19:14.554 --> 19:15.855
Want to have some fun?

19:15.888 --> 19:18.658
-I'm already having fun.
-Stop the car.

19:18.691 --> 19:20.293
-Why?
-Just do it.

19:20.327 --> 19:23.196
[ Tires screech ]

19:23.230 --> 19:24.297
Thank you.

19:24.331 --> 19:27.834
Don't worry. We're the only car
on the road right now.

19:27.867 --> 19:29.902
Put your left foot
on the brake.

19:29.936 --> 19:31.771
Mm, okay.

19:31.804 --> 19:33.306
There we go.

19:33.340 --> 19:36.243
Now hold it all the way down.
There you go.

19:36.276 --> 19:39.879
Okay, now floor the gas
with your right foot.

19:40.580 --> 19:42.349
[ Engine revs ]

19:42.382 --> 19:44.684
I-I don't know about this.

19:44.717 --> 19:45.985
No, it's okay.
It's okay.

19:46.018 --> 19:49.789
Now slowly ease your left foot
off the brake...

19:50.890 --> 19:52.792
...until you hear...

19:52.825 --> 19:54.594
[ Tires squealing ]
...this.

19:54.627 --> 19:56.529
I smell smoke.

19:56.563 --> 19:58.331
Yeah,
that's the point, Shaun.

19:58.365 --> 20:01.268
It's burning rubber.
Do it again.

20:02.802 --> 20:03.936
-Okay.
-[ Chuckles ]

20:04.637 --> 20:07.440
[ Engine revving,
tires squealing ]

20:10.443 --> 20:11.878
Now, this is fun.

20:11.911 --> 20:13.980
[ Engine revving,
tires squealing ]

20:14.013 --> 20:15.382
Okay, that's enough.

20:15.415 --> 20:17.450
We need some rubber left
to get us home.

20:17.484 --> 20:19.886
I am burning rubber.

20:19.919 --> 20:21.721
Okay, Shaun,
it's time to stop.
Okay.

20:23.656 --> 20:25.692
Shaun, take your other foot
off the gas!

20:25.725 --> 20:27.527
Shaun, look out!

20:28.461 --> 20:30.563
It's the other foot!
Other foot!

20:30.597 --> 20:31.731
It's the other foot!
It's the other foot!

20:31.764 --> 20:33.366
It's the other foot!

20:35.802 --> 20:37.937
Dr. Ko and I
have been working for months

20:37.970 --> 20:39.772
to map the structure
of Jenny and Katie's brain.
Mm-hmm.

20:39.806 --> 20:41.541
-Don't you mean "brains"?
-Actually,

20:41.574 --> 20:43.776
while different regions operate
independently for each sister,

20:43.810 --> 20:45.445
there is
a single brain mass.

20:45.478 --> 20:47.447
That's why all their
previous neurosurgeons

20:47.480 --> 20:49.015
insisted separation
was impossible.

20:49.048 --> 20:51.618
The real problem won't be
dividing their brains

20:51.651 --> 20:53.753
but dividing their veins.

20:53.786 --> 20:56.723
They share a single
sagittal sinus vein.

20:56.756 --> 20:58.391
Melendez:
Which we'll give to Jenny.

20:58.425 --> 21:00.593
Then we'll create
a new one for Katie

21:00.627 --> 21:02.061
using a grafted vein
from her leg.

21:02.094 --> 21:04.697
Nice. You've gotten them
up to speed fast.

21:04.731 --> 21:06.933
Well, with 6 months of prep
to do in 12 hours,

21:06.966 --> 21:08.401
it was their only choice.

21:08.435 --> 21:10.036
So, let's get started.

21:10.069 --> 21:11.338
-I crashed.
-We didn't.

21:11.371 --> 21:12.539
We just --
-Yes, I-I crashed.

21:12.572 --> 21:14.040
I hit something.
-Shaun. Shaun.

21:14.073 --> 21:15.942
I hit something.
I did. I hit something.

21:15.975 --> 21:16.976
-Shaun, you --
-I know I did.

21:17.009 --> 21:18.745
-I felt it. I crashed.
-Shaun, you didn't crash.

21:18.778 --> 21:19.912
-Yes.
-You just drove off the road...

21:19.946 --> 21:20.880
-No.
-...and it was totally my fault.

21:20.913 --> 21:22.515
No, you're wrong.
Nuh-unh. I hit something.

21:22.549 --> 21:23.350
-No, you didn't.
-I felt it.

21:23.383 --> 21:24.083
I crashed.
-No, Shaun, look at me.

21:24.116 --> 21:24.917
-I crashed.
-Calm down. Calm.

21:24.951 --> 21:27.687
-Okay. Okay.
-Look at me. Look at me.

21:27.720 --> 21:28.921
Breathe.

21:28.955 --> 21:32.325
Whatever happened, whatever
you felt, you did nothing wrong.

21:32.359 --> 21:34.927
It was all my fault,
okay?

21:34.961 --> 21:37.897
[ Breathing deeply ]

21:37.930 --> 21:41.501
Okay. Dr. Glassman --
He was right.

21:41.534 --> 21:44.804
I-I should not be allowed
to drive.

21:44.837 --> 21:46.839
No, no.

21:46.873 --> 21:49.509
[ Sighs ]

21:51.077 --> 21:51.911
Shaun.

21:51.944 --> 21:55.014
No, I'm not going to drive,
thank you.

21:55.047 --> 21:57.884
Yeah, I -- I know.
No one is.

21:57.917 --> 22:00.520
'Cause you were right.
We did hit something.

22:00.553 --> 22:06.058
**

22:06.092 --> 22:11.798
**

22:11.831 --> 22:14.467
[ Monitor beeping ]

22:16.002 --> 22:17.604
Everything
is still looking good.

22:17.637 --> 22:19.972
If you need anything
during the night,

22:20.006 --> 22:21.040
just press
your call button.

22:21.073 --> 22:23.843
Is Jenny asleep?

22:23.876 --> 22:24.877
Yeah.

22:24.911 --> 22:26.379
Where's Dr. Andrews?

22:26.413 --> 22:29.916
He is with Dr. Ko
and Dr. Melendez.

22:29.949 --> 22:32.819
They're working to
finalize the surgical
protocol for tomorrow.

22:32.852 --> 22:35.388
I need to talk to him.

22:35.422 --> 22:37.624
Is there anything
I can do?

22:40.059 --> 22:41.594
I changed my mind.

22:41.628 --> 22:45.364
I don't want to do
the separation surgery.

22:46.899 --> 22:48.668
I'll go find him
right away.

22:48.701 --> 22:55.041
**

22:57.544 --> 22:59.879
I understand she's scared,
but without this surgery,

22:59.912 --> 23:01.514
there is a good chance
both of them die.

23:01.548 --> 23:02.915
Have you talked
to the mother?

23:02.949 --> 23:05.184
She refuses to weigh in,
insists it's their decision.

23:05.217 --> 23:06.853
Let me try
and talk to her.

23:06.886 --> 23:08.154
I don't think
that's a good idea.

23:08.187 --> 23:09.622
You invented
the technique

23:09.656 --> 23:11.424
you're gonna use
to separate them.

23:11.458 --> 23:12.792
So?

23:12.825 --> 23:14.994
So she's not even close
to objective.

23:15.027 --> 23:17.664
Okay, now is not the time
to be worrying about lawsuits.

23:17.697 --> 23:18.598
That's my job.

23:18.631 --> 23:20.700
And our job is saving
these girls' lives.

23:20.733 --> 23:24.671
Okay, take it easy.
We're all on the same team here.

23:25.237 --> 23:27.440
I'll talk to her.
-You've already talked to her.

23:27.474 --> 23:28.708
I will try again.

23:31.544 --> 23:32.845
Browne should do it.

23:33.846 --> 23:34.847
Me?

23:34.881 --> 23:39.018
We need someone
that an 18-year-old girl trusts.

23:39.051 --> 23:41.087
She's also the best communicator
out of all of us.

23:41.120 --> 23:46.726
**

23:46.759 --> 23:49.529
Okay.

23:49.562 --> 23:50.797
We'll give Katie the night
to think it over.

23:50.830 --> 23:52.031
Browne, you'll talk to her
in the morning.

23:52.064 --> 23:53.500
Get her to consent
to this surgery.

23:53.533 --> 23:56.168
And if I'm not able
to do that?

23:56.202 --> 23:59.105
**

23:59.138 --> 24:02.909
It's not a big deal.
Cars break.

24:02.942 --> 24:05.845
That's why God
makes mechanics -- and booze.

24:05.878 --> 24:07.647
Two shots of tequila,
please.

24:07.680 --> 24:09.716
I'm not thirsty.

24:09.749 --> 24:13.052
You don't drink tequila
because you're thirsty.

24:13.886 --> 24:16.155
Have you ever been drunk?

24:17.289 --> 24:18.758
Never?

24:18.791 --> 24:22.962
Eight years of college
a-and not one frat party?

24:22.995 --> 24:25.832
Tailgating?
Your roommate's 21st birthday?

24:25.865 --> 24:27.033
What is your job?

24:27.066 --> 24:29.636
Now you're interested
in my job?

24:29.669 --> 24:30.837
Yes.

24:30.870 --> 24:32.972
I'm an
automotive engineer.

24:33.005 --> 24:35.875
I work for a start-up
that's developing new designs

24:35.908 --> 24:37.577
for self-driving cars.

24:37.610 --> 24:39.145
Do you like it?

24:39.178 --> 24:41.147
No.

24:41.180 --> 24:42.649
Oh.

24:42.682 --> 24:44.551
I like to build things,

24:44.584 --> 24:48.287
not to sit in endless meetings
talking about building things.

24:48.320 --> 24:50.723
Thank you.

24:50.757 --> 24:52.158
Perfect timing.

24:52.191 --> 24:56.228
We are supposed to be
forgetting about work.

24:56.763 --> 24:58.731
[ Clears throat ]

24:58.765 --> 25:03.135
For living happy
because you're a long time dead.

25:03.169 --> 25:09.609
**

25:09.642 --> 25:15.882
**

25:15.915 --> 25:18.184
It's...good.

25:18.217 --> 25:21.688
Oh, my God. You have to be
the first person in history

25:21.721 --> 25:24.090
to actually like
their first tequila shot.
It's good.

25:24.123 --> 25:26.058
-Do you want another?
-Okay.

25:26.092 --> 25:29.061
-Yes.
-Tequila. Stat.

25:29.095 --> 25:30.529
Yes!

25:41.207 --> 25:42.642
What?

25:44.644 --> 25:46.245
Sorry.
I'm just zoned out.

25:46.278 --> 25:48.180
We should break this off.

25:48.214 --> 25:50.149
There's only so much studying
you can do.

25:50.182 --> 25:53.319
[ Sighs ]

25:57.724 --> 25:59.225
Do you want kids?

26:00.159 --> 26:03.195
Sorry.
That's none of my business.

26:03.229 --> 26:05.097
No, it's [chuckles]

26:05.131 --> 26:07.734
it's just not a question
I was expecting.

26:07.767 --> 26:10.870
Jessica just told me
she doesn't. Ever.

26:10.903 --> 26:11.838
Wow.

26:11.871 --> 26:13.339
It doesn't make any sense.

26:13.372 --> 26:16.643
She would be
such an amazing mother.

26:16.676 --> 26:20.212
I guess she's lucky she realized
before it's too late.

26:20.246 --> 26:23.650
Some women don't.

26:23.683 --> 26:25.752
My mom was definitely
one of those.

26:25.785 --> 26:28.688
-Sorry. I didn't mean to --
-No, it's okay.

26:28.721 --> 26:33.626
Water under the bridge...
that nearly drowned me.

26:33.660 --> 26:35.594
It was a long time ago.

26:36.362 --> 26:37.964
I don't know what to do.

26:39.298 --> 26:43.035
I can't imagine
my life without her,

26:43.069 --> 26:47.006
but I also can't imagine
a life without...

26:49.108 --> 26:51.077
I'm sorry.

26:51.110 --> 26:53.212
[ Chuckles ] Again,
this is not your problem.

26:53.245 --> 26:55.882
-It's okay.
-Go. Goodbye.

26:55.915 --> 27:02.421
**

27:02.454 --> 27:06.158
Finding someone you can't
imagine a life without,

27:06.192 --> 27:08.394
it's hard.

27:08.427 --> 27:13.065
I know it's a clichÃ©,
but it is true.

27:16.302 --> 27:18.705
Good night.

27:22.241 --> 27:23.876
Good night.

27:23.910 --> 27:25.712
[ Off key ]
* Islands in the stream

27:25.745 --> 27:27.714
* That is what we are

27:27.747 --> 27:29.348
* No one in between

27:29.381 --> 27:31.350
* How can we be wrong?

27:31.383 --> 27:33.352
* Sail away with me

27:33.385 --> 27:35.387
* To another world

27:35.421 --> 27:39.792
* And we rely on each other,
ah-ha *

27:39.826 --> 27:43.763
* From one lover
to another, ha-ha *
* Oh, oh

27:43.796 --> 27:48.801
* I can't live without you

27:49.836 --> 27:52.705
[ Knock on door ]

28:02.381 --> 28:03.816
I love you.

28:03.850 --> 28:07.386
I love you, too.

28:07.419 --> 28:13.292
So, I will volunteer with
foster kids, coach youth sports.

28:13.325 --> 28:15.828
There are other ways
that I can be a father figure

28:15.862 --> 28:17.964
without actually being
a father.

28:17.997 --> 28:23.770
**

28:23.803 --> 28:26.372
[ Slurring ] In one day,
I taught you how to
play hooky from work,

28:26.405 --> 28:28.474
how to drive,
how to drink,

28:28.507 --> 28:30.109
and how to totally
rock the house in karaoke.

28:30.142 --> 28:33.946
No, y-you did not teach me
to drive very well at all.

28:33.980 --> 28:35.381
-Ohhh.
-At all.

28:35.414 --> 28:38.150
-Oh, how dare you.
-I-I-I crashed.

28:38.184 --> 28:39.418
No, you didn't crash.

28:39.451 --> 28:42.088
You hit a rock
that should not have been there.

28:42.121 --> 28:43.990
The whole point
of a road shoulder

28:44.023 --> 28:46.125
is to provide
a buffer zone.

28:46.158 --> 28:48.360
Who the hell desi--
designs a buffer zone

28:48.394 --> 28:50.296
with a huge rock in it,
you know?

28:50.329 --> 28:53.432
They should be fired.

28:54.533 --> 28:57.269
O-Okay, hold it right there,
partner.

28:57.303 --> 29:00.339
I got one more thing
to teach you.

29:00.372 --> 29:01.507
What is it?

29:01.540 --> 29:05.744
The proper way
to end a date.

29:07.446 --> 29:11.083
Tell me you hope I had
a good time tonight.

29:11.583 --> 29:13.920
Go ahead.

29:16.222 --> 29:19.125
I hope you had
a good time tonight.

29:19.158 --> 29:22.128
I did. I had
a very nice time tonight.

29:22.161 --> 29:25.331
You're really fun
to sing karaoke with.

29:26.498 --> 29:28.868
Now tell me
I'm really fun, too,

29:28.901 --> 29:31.337
and that you hope
we can do it again soon.

29:32.371 --> 29:36.542
Y-Y-You're really fun,
too.

29:36.575 --> 29:37.910
Thank you.

29:37.944 --> 29:39.979
I hope that
we can do it again soon.

29:40.012 --> 29:42.815
Now open the door for me.

29:45.184 --> 29:46.853
[ Door creaks ]

29:46.886 --> 29:50.089
Now,
if I just walk in,

29:50.122 --> 29:52.491
don't bother trying
for a second date.

29:52.524 --> 29:54.026
It's a swing and a miss,
not a big deal.

29:54.060 --> 29:54.927
It happens to everyone.

29:54.961 --> 29:57.196
But if I don't walk in,

29:57.229 --> 29:59.866
if I just stand there
in front of you

29:59.899 --> 30:02.601
like I don't really
want to go inside,

30:02.634 --> 30:07.006
like I'm doing right now,
then you have to kiss me.

30:07.039 --> 30:12.011
**

30:12.044 --> 30:14.013
Kiss me, Shaun.

30:14.046 --> 30:22.621
**

30:22.654 --> 30:31.463
**

30:31.497 --> 30:34.867
Have you ever
done that before?

30:35.968 --> 30:39.005
Uh, no, no, no, no.

30:39.038 --> 30:41.507
[ Chuckles ]
Well, you're pretty good at it.

30:41.540 --> 30:42.608
You want to do it again?

30:42.641 --> 30:44.944
Yes, but...

30:44.977 --> 30:47.146
But what?

30:47.179 --> 30:52.218
**

30:52.251 --> 30:54.186
[ Vomiting ]

30:55.487 --> 30:57.556
Oof.

31:01.327 --> 31:02.161
I know it's frightening.

31:02.194 --> 31:04.964
You've already been through
so much.

31:06.498 --> 31:07.633
I'm not scared.

31:07.666 --> 31:13.172
I just think, "What if this is
how we're meant to be?"

31:13.205 --> 31:15.374
Maybe we're better as one.

31:20.512 --> 31:23.649
I grew up
in a trailer, um,

31:23.682 --> 31:27.586
with, uh, my mom telling me
every day

31:27.619 --> 31:29.956
that I was
no better than her

31:29.989 --> 31:33.292
and that
I would never do anything,

31:33.325 --> 31:35.161
I'd never be anyone,

31:35.194 --> 31:37.663
and I...

31:37.696 --> 31:40.266
I hated being there.

31:41.433 --> 31:43.936
But when I finally left,

31:43.970 --> 31:52.044
walking out of the dirty,
disgusting double-wide...

31:54.280 --> 31:57.416
...was the hardest thing
I've ever done.

31:58.584 --> 32:00.486
Wait, so,
am I the awful mom

32:00.519 --> 32:02.554
or the disgusting trailer
in this story?

32:02.588 --> 32:06.325
[ Laughter ]
Um...

32:08.627 --> 32:12.531
It's amazing what you've
accomplished so far.

32:12.564 --> 32:13.665
It really is.

32:13.699 --> 32:19.305
But you can be
so much more,

32:19.338 --> 32:28.647
and with the freedom
to just finally be yourself.

32:29.148 --> 32:31.683
Just yourself.

32:31.717 --> 32:38.657
**

32:38.690 --> 32:41.693
[ Sighs ]
Katie's back on board.

32:41.727 --> 32:43.529
Told you.

32:43.562 --> 32:45.697
She's very persuasive.

32:55.141 --> 32:56.442
Shaun?

32:56.475 --> 33:01.613
**

33:01.647 --> 33:05.651
**

33:05.684 --> 33:08.620
I feel disgusting.

33:08.654 --> 33:10.256
You're just hungover.

33:10.289 --> 33:14.160
You are never gonna want me
to kiss you ever again.

33:14.193 --> 33:18.130
If I had brushed my teeth
before I rushed out here,

33:18.164 --> 33:21.533
I'd ask you to do it again
right now.

33:22.501 --> 33:25.037
Why are you so hard
on yourself?

33:27.339 --> 33:30.642
I'm sure you got made fun of
a lot when you were a kid,

33:30.676 --> 33:33.145
and that leaves a mark.

33:33.179 --> 33:34.180
I know.

33:34.213 --> 33:38.684
But you gotta shake it off,
rub some dirt on it.

33:40.652 --> 33:44.256
You're never gonna be happy
if you constantly live in fear.

33:44.290 --> 33:53.665
**

33:53.699 --> 33:55.601
We need to talk.
Look, I have nothing
to say to you.

33:55.634 --> 33:57.569
Well, then,
you can just listen.

33:57.603 --> 33:59.571
You are not a victim.
Not even close.

33:59.605 --> 34:02.274
But you will be
unless you convince Andrews

34:02.308 --> 34:03.309
to reinstate Jared.

34:03.342 --> 34:05.177
Are you threatening me?

34:05.211 --> 34:07.713
No, I'm just informing you
that there is no way

34:07.746 --> 34:09.815
that I'm the only resident
that you tried to intimidate

34:09.848 --> 34:11.049
into having sex
with you.

34:11.083 --> 34:14.786
And I will make it my mission
in life to find every single one

34:14.820 --> 34:16.555
and get them to file
a complaint against you

34:16.588 --> 34:18.524
unless Jared
gets his job back.

34:18.557 --> 34:20.126
And what makes you
so sure

34:20.159 --> 34:22.394
Andrews cares
what I have to say?
I'm not.

34:22.428 --> 34:24.396
But either Jared's career
gets saved,

34:24.430 --> 34:26.398
or yours gets destroyed.

34:26.432 --> 34:28.367
Either way
is a win for me.

34:28.400 --> 34:34.740
**

34:34.773 --> 34:36.742
15 blade.

34:36.775 --> 34:43.849
**

34:43.882 --> 34:46.452
Removing the first balloon
tissue expander.

34:46.485 --> 34:52.524
**

34:52.558 --> 34:58.564
**

34:58.597 --> 35:00.699
One down. Five to go.

35:00.732 --> 35:07.105
**

35:08.540 --> 35:10.709
[ Water running ]

35:10.742 --> 35:20.652
**

35:20.686 --> 35:24.190
Glassman: Hi, Shaun.
It's me again.

35:24.223 --> 35:26.925
Um [sighs] you know,

35:26.958 --> 35:30.729
Do-- Dr. Andrews has never
really been in your corner,

35:30.762 --> 35:34.833
and your absence is causing
a real problem.

35:34.866 --> 35:37.503
Please call me
before it's too late.

35:37.536 --> 35:42.241
Or at least [sighs] call me
and let me know where you are

35:42.274 --> 35:44.610
'cause I'm worried.

35:46.912 --> 35:48.614
[ Cellphone clicks ]

35:48.647 --> 35:50.949
Ko: The cavitron
allows us to use

35:50.982 --> 35:55.421
a low-frequency sound wave
to separate them

35:55.454 --> 35:58.924
so that we don't damage the
healthy tissue in the process.

35:58.957 --> 36:01.693
I still can't tell where
Katie starts and Jenny ends.

36:01.727 --> 36:07.633
Mm-hmm.
The imaging is a huge help.

36:08.567 --> 36:10.269
But once the patient
is opened,

36:10.302 --> 36:13.905
it's kind of like
backcountry skiing.

36:13.939 --> 36:15.907
It's never the same
on top.

36:15.941 --> 36:17.976
What you want
to focus on

36:18.009 --> 36:21.413
is the terrain
you know is underneath.

36:29.955 --> 36:34.260
[ Cellphone beeps, Jill Andrews'
"Get Up, Get On" plays ]

36:37.496 --> 36:44.236
* Here, here we are

36:44.270 --> 36:50.876
* And all we got,
we had from the start *

36:51.577 --> 36:54.346
* So get up, get up,
get up, and go on *

36:54.380 --> 36:56.415
Cut.

36:57.683 --> 37:00.452
* Keep your head up, love

37:00.486 --> 37:03.855
* Keep your heart strong
Grafted sagittal's
in place.

37:03.889 --> 37:05.257
Let's remove the clamps.

37:05.291 --> 37:09.928
* Oooooh, ooh, ooh

37:09.961 --> 37:12.431
Okay.

37:12.464 --> 37:15.801
* Cover up the war inside
Looks good. No leaks.

37:15.834 --> 37:18.570
Now the moment of truth.
Scissors.

37:18.604 --> 37:21.873
* The most beautiful part of
ourselves is the part we hide *
Dr. Ko, would you like
to do the honors?

37:21.907 --> 37:24.843
Mm. Definitely.

37:25.977 --> 37:28.814
* So get up, get up,
get up, and get on *

37:28.847 --> 37:30.316
Can we get
a little more room?

37:30.349 --> 37:32.684
Coming right up.

37:32.718 --> 37:38.457
* Just a little belief
to shake off the doubt *

37:39.925 --> 37:44.363
* Oooooh, ooh, ooh

37:44.396 --> 37:46.365
[ Sighs ]
And then there were two.

37:46.398 --> 37:49.435
* It's building up

37:49.468 --> 37:54.306
* It's been building up
for so long *
[ All sigh ]

37:58.744 --> 38:01.647
Thanks for taking me
on a road trip.

38:01.680 --> 38:03.081
I feel a lot better.

38:03.114 --> 38:07.085
I think I'm ready
to talk to Dr. Glassman.

38:07.118 --> 38:11.923
Yeah, I feel much better, too,
and ready to talk to my boss.

38:11.957 --> 38:14.560
What do you have to talk
to your boss about?

38:14.593 --> 38:16.027
He offered me
a promotion.

38:16.061 --> 38:19.465
Will you be making
$1 million?

38:19.498 --> 38:21.400
Ha-ha. Very funny.

38:21.433 --> 38:24.970
I make $70,000 now, and
the new position pays $90,000,

38:25.003 --> 38:28.740
but I'm not gonna take it.

38:28.774 --> 38:30.108
Why not?

38:30.141 --> 38:32.778
It pays $20,000 more.

38:32.811 --> 38:36.882
Yeah, I get the math, Shaun,
but just taking this trip and --

38:36.915 --> 38:40.352
and you have inspired me
to do something

38:40.386 --> 38:41.720
that I've been thinking about
for a really long time,

38:41.753 --> 38:44.656
but I've just been
too scared to do it.

38:44.690 --> 38:47.359
I'm gonna quit my job.

38:47.393 --> 38:48.527
[ Both laugh ]
You're so silly.

38:48.560 --> 38:50.095
What would you do
during the day?

38:50.128 --> 38:51.229
Rebuild old cars.

38:51.262 --> 38:55.601
No more conference calls.
No more never-ending meetings.

38:55.634 --> 39:01.507
The only thing I'm not looking
forward to is, uh -- is moving.

39:01.540 --> 39:03.008
Why would you move?

39:03.041 --> 39:07.579
Because that's where the shop
that I'm gonna work at is.

39:07.613 --> 39:08.947
I got the Striped Tomato.

39:08.980 --> 39:11.517
My brother, Donny,
got Grandpa Rod's shop

39:11.550 --> 39:13.985
in Hershey, Pennsylvania.

39:14.019 --> 39:19.157
It's been over a year,
but every time I drive his car,

39:19.190 --> 39:23.562
I...keep thinking,

39:23.595 --> 39:26.532
"You know, I don't need
a more impressive title

39:26.565 --> 39:27.999
or $1 million."

39:28.033 --> 39:31.169
He would take me fishing
in Alaska every summer,

39:31.202 --> 39:32.771
skiing every winter break.

39:32.804 --> 39:35.841
I haven't taken more than
one day off in four years

39:35.874 --> 39:37.075
because I always work.

39:37.108 --> 39:38.977
It never stops.

39:39.010 --> 39:43.949
And just taking this trip with
you made me realize I, uh --

39:43.982 --> 39:49.821
I want to enjoy my life,
you know?

39:52.090 --> 39:54.726
Okay, what?
Say something.

39:54.760 --> 40:00.065
**

40:00.098 --> 40:05.604
**

40:05.637 --> 40:07.105
Oh.

40:07.138 --> 40:09.007
You're...

40:09.040 --> 40:11.142
[ Bell dings ]

40:11.176 --> 40:14.880
[ Sighs ]

40:16.982 --> 40:19.017
[ Cellphone ringing ]

40:22.954 --> 40:24.490
[ Exhales sharply ]

40:24.523 --> 40:26.057
[ Cellphone beeps ]
Hello?

40:26.091 --> 40:28.894
Jared, this is Dr. Andrews.
Do you have a moment?

40:28.927 --> 40:30.529
Yeah, of course.

40:30.562 --> 40:33.098
Dr. Coyle approached me
today.

40:33.131 --> 40:34.466
He told me
that he feels awful

40:34.500 --> 40:36.568
about the way
he treated Dr. Browne

40:36.602 --> 40:38.837
and how it came
to affect you,

40:38.870 --> 40:41.607
and he asked me to reconsider
your termination.

40:42.073 --> 40:43.174
You should also know

40:43.208 --> 40:43.909
that Dr. Melendez spoke
in support of you, as well.

40:43.942 --> 40:47.012
Thank you
for letting me know.

40:47.045 --> 40:49.114
I was impressed by
the integrity you demonstrated

40:49.147 --> 40:52.984
by taking full responsibility
for your actions.

40:53.018 --> 40:54.820
And I'm certainly willing
to make that clear

40:54.853 --> 40:56.555
to any administrators
at another hospital

40:56.588 --> 40:58.490
if you need me
as a reference,

40:58.524 --> 41:02.127
but I won't
reinstate you.

41:02.160 --> 41:03.595
Physical assault
is a line

41:03.629 --> 41:05.731
I'm just not willing
to let anyone cross.

41:05.764 --> 41:08.033
I understand.

41:08.066 --> 41:10.569
I'm sorry.

41:10.602 --> 41:12.571
Take care.

41:12.604 --> 41:14.640
[ Cellphone beeps ]
[ Sighs ]

41:14.673 --> 41:18.810
**

41:18.844 --> 41:20.912
When will they wake up?

41:20.946 --> 41:26.918
**

41:26.952 --> 41:29.020
They should've already.

41:31.056 --> 41:34.225
Shaun?

41:34.259 --> 41:36.061
[ Sighs ]

41:36.094 --> 41:39.097
Shaun.

41:45.937 --> 41:48.574
[ Cellphone clicks ]

42:06.858 --> 42:08.860
[ Cellphone beeps ]

42:08.894 --> 42:11.597
* Our sharp teeth
are the only light *

42:11.630 --> 42:14.966
* I drink the whole moon dry *

42:15.000 --> 42:16.868
* 'Cause all my friends
are metalheads *

42:16.902 --> 42:18.670
* Swear they'll never
catch us dead *

42:18.704 --> 42:21.873
* Split up
when the police come *

42:21.907 --> 42:25.844
* Yeah, running used to
get me high, high *

42:25.877 --> 42:27.913
* Now I only feel tired *

42:30.315 --> 42:38.223
**

42:38.256 --> 42:46.131
**

42:46.164 --> 42:54.105
**

42:54.139 --> 43:04.049
**
